  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 7a9e7d0954553594ebb4351359a0d4e5, type: 3}
  m_Name: Speech_Heather_Opening
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ClientSpeech
  Clip: {fileID: 8300000, guid: c187895de942d3742b335d829fac5d1a, type: 3}
  Subtitles: "Postmodernist theory is of course more important than religion at this
    point - If everyone just subscribed to tubular Marxism, we could solve the problems
    of the universe. World peace is an admirable solution, but isn\u2019t the idea
    of \u2018peace\u2019 somewhat problematic? It excludes civilizations that have
    a long-term non-violent definition of peace, and privileges those that count
    short-term low-violence policies, such as systems of authority. I don\u2019t
    really enjoy the idea of suffering in a system together with a bunch of non-egalitarians
    - It feels really beneath me, you know? On what level should I just up and punish
    her for not getting the program?"
